                  <interp inst="t18260406-281-crimeloc1521" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260406-281-off1517 t18260406-281-crimeloc1521"></join> - I had seen it ten minutes before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-281-person1526">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BOLTON
               <interp inst="t18260406-281-person1526" type="surname" value="BOLTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-281-person1526" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-281-person1526" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I was going into Whitecross-street, and saw the two prisoners following four gentlemen - I saw Orange soon after come round a waggon, with this handkerchief in his hand - I caught hold of him, and took up the handkerchief, which he threw under the waggon - I could not see that Mr. Brough was one of the gentlemen they were following.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-281-person1527">
                  JOHN 
                  FOWELL
               <interp inst="t18260406-281-person1527" type="surname" value="FOWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-281-person1527" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-281-person1527" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in Whitecross-street, and saw them - I saw Orange take the handkerchief out of Mr. Brough's pocket, and put it into his bosom half way - he ran into the road; Bolton took him, and he threw it under the waggon; I did not see Johnson do any thing.</p>
               <p>ORANGE'S Defence. I came up to a waggon, and I ran to get out of the way.</p>
               <p>JOHNSON'S Defence. I was running by a coach, and a waggon was coming in - the officer took hold of me, and said I had been with Orange, but I had not seen him do any thing.</p>
               <p>ORANGE - <rs id="t18260406-281-verdict1522" type="verdictDescription">
